  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Start Fund Bangladesh Rohingya Reponse Fires</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Background information on Fire outbreak in the Cox Bazaar refugee camps. 
 
 Affected locations:
 
 One of our WFP Food Distribution outlets- Balukhali-2 (Camp-8W) completely burnt
 
 Outlet-3-Maynarghona (10, 11, 12, 18)-Host Community (No damage)
 
 Outlet-4-Camp (17, 18 partial, 10 partial, 8W partial)
 
 Outlet-5-Camp 20 Extension (20 and 20 Extension)-No damage
 
 In WASH, a water-network which has been built along with UNICEF has been affected badly in Camp 8E and the water points have been damaged. 
 
 In Education, it has been reported that none of the Multi-purpose Centres(MPCs) run by BRCR have been affected and based on the request by UNICEF, some of the MPCs will be kept open for shelters to accommodate the victims.
 
 In Camp-9, few hundreds of cement bags(Photo attached) and construction materials and tools(property of WFP-DRR) have been damaged. 
 
 One of BRCR&apos;s women staff has been traumatized of the incident and steps taken by P&amp;C providing her counseling and she is recovering.
 
  Plan of action:
 
 1. Soon after we came to know about the fire and its severity, evacuated all the staff and the Rohingya volunteers, facilitators to a safe place and to their homes; 
 
 2. Planning to conduct a rapid assessment in the camps by different teams and a report will be available for sharing to donors and stakeholders by COB today; 
 
 3. Some of our Education Learning Centres in the affected areas will be opened as temporary shelters enabling people to stay safe and recuperate; 4. Based on the request of WFP, Yesterday, we distributed 4031 cartons of High Energy biscuits to affected people using our staff(23) till 12 am; 5. BRCR from today (23rd March) onward until further notice will be serving energy biscuits for breakfast and hot food for Lunch and Dinner for 50,000 people. 
 
 6. Informed donors about the fire incident and the rapid assessment report will be shared to them at the earliest; 
 
 7. Planning to initiate a discussion today with WFP-DRR to rebuild the shelters for the Fire Incident victims.</narrative>
  </description>
